%S A380202 4,8,14,19,24,28,34,40,45,49,56,63,72,81,89,97,107,116,125,132,142,
%T A380202 152,164,175,186,196,208,220,231,238,248,258,270,281,292,302,314,326,
%U A380202 337,343,352,361,372,382,392,401,412,423,433,439,448,457,468,478,488,497,508,519,529,535,544,553,564,574,584,593,604,615,625
%N A380202 Number of card moves to deal n cards using the SpellUnder-Down dealing.
%C A380202 In SpellUnder-Down dealing, we spell the number of the next card, putting a card under for each letter in the number, then we deal the next card. So we start with putting 3 cards under, for O-N-E, then deal, then 3 under for T-W-O, then deal, then 5 under for T-H-R-E-E, then deal. The dealing sequence is highly irregular because it depends on English spelling. The dealing pattern starts: UUUDUUUDUUUUUD .
%H A380202 Eric Huang, Tanya Khovanova, Timur Kilybayev, Ryan Li, Brandon Ni, Leone Seidel, Samarth Sharma, Nathan Sheffield, Vivek Varanasi, Alice Yin, Boya Yun, and William Zelevinsky, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2509.11395">Card Dealing Math</a>, arXiv:2509.11395 [math.NT], 2025. See p. 17.
%F A380202 a(n) = A067278(n) + n.
%e A380202 The dealing pattern to deal three cards is UUUDUUUDUUUUUD. It contains 14 letters, thus, a(3) = 14.
%o A380202 (Python)
%o A380202 from num2words import num2words
%o A380202 from itertools import count, islice
%o A380202 def n2w(n): return "".join(c for c in num2words(n).replace(" and", "") if c.isalpha())
%o A380202 def agen():
%o A380202     tot = 0
%o A380202     for n in count(1):
%o A380202         tot += len(n2w(n))
%o A380202         yield tot + n
%o A380202 print(list(islice(agen(), 69))) # _Michael S. Branicky_, Jun 02 2026
%Y A380202 Cf. A005589, A006257, A067278, A225381, A321298, A378635, A380201, A380204, A380246, A380247, A380248.
